latestPosts.caption:
I spent much of my teens and twenties watching rugby at the Bombay Gym — I was dating @homster who was quite a star on the field ( and off it 😉!) and Saturdays were all about the game, blood, sweat, cheers, and then the bar where the weekend really began!

(Must scroll! ➡️)

So being at the Andheri Sports Complex yesterday for the @rugbypremierleague , led by my dear friend @rahulbose7 — who’s played with more heart (and broken noses) than anyone I know — was deeply special.

As President of the Indian Rugby Federation, what Rahul’s done for the sport in India is incredible — building it from the ground up with quiet determination and unwavering passion.

It’s a game of grit, strategy, and true sportsmanship — and I am especially thrilled that so many of our amazing women are playing rugby today.

Also, full cheer squad mode for my darling @chait.sinh , who was absolutely brilliant as the tournament’s official commentator!

Thank you, Rahul — proud and grateful to be there, always cheering you on.

@gmr_sports

latestPosts.caption:
Behind every unforgettable Met Gala look is a story told in carats. Anaita Shroff Adajania unveils the artistry behind her red carpet vision—where every real diamond isn’t just worn, it speaks. 

#MetGala2025 #NaturalDiamonds #RealDiamonds #heerahaisadakeliye #DeBeersGroup

One for the books 🫶

A tribute to the spirit of self-expression,  courage and creativity; to the power of fashion as a tool of resistance and self-definition; to legacy and to new beginnings.

We built our vision of “Bravehearts” on the spirit of the Black Dandy — they who challenge norms and reshape culture, with a spirit of grace and strength,  and the drive for self-expression and recognition. They who dare to be different, who celebrate individuality, and who use fashion as a tool for empowerment and social commentary. 

Enveloped in a dramatic white cape, echoing André Leon Talley’s iconic 2010 Met Gala look, sits the stunning gold breastplates of two hearts connected by a delicate jewelled umbilical cord, symbolizing the unbreakable bond between mother and child.
The look transcends mere aesthetics, representing the intricate dance between inherited identity and reimagined culture across generations.

I’m grateful to have collaborated with the best team– @ggpanther, @anaitashroffadajania, @mehakoberoi @gauravguptaofficial – who made my met debut so memorable 🙌🏻

And my dearest friend @karinachowgule and her wonderful team who captured these precious moments 💛
